# verify-kit conventions

The canonical agent rules live in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md). Cursor-specific notes:

- Run `just verify --quick` before claiming any change is "done".
- `verify-kit list-checks` enumerates available checks; `verify-kit describe`
  shows the JSON Schema for every check.
- Lint/typecheck failures are clickable in the Problems panel via the
  `.vscode/tasks.json` problem matchers — open it via `Ctrl+Shift+B`.
- MCP tools are available via `verify-kit mcp serve` — see `.cursor/mcp.json`
  for the auto-registered server.
- Do not write to relative paths from harness code (`Path(".verify/...")` is
  always wrong); always thread `cwd` through. See AGENTS.md §Tool conventions.
